# Tailwind CSS v3 to v4 Upgrade

## When to use

- Migrating Tailwind CSS from v3 to v4
- Converting `tailwind.config.js` to CSS-based `@theme` configuration
- Replacing `@tailwind base/components/utilities` with `@import "tailwindcss"`
- Removing PostCSS and autoprefixer after Tailwind v4 upgrade
- Setting up `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin in vite.config.js
- Migrating content paths from JS config to `@source` directives in CSS
- Converting JS plugin requires to CSS `@import` (e.g., `@import "@tailwindcss/forms"`)
- Updating opacity classes from `bg-opacity-50` to slash syntax `bg-black/50`
- Using new gradient syntax (`bg-linear-to-r`, `bg-conic`, `bg-radial`)
- Upgrading Tailwind for Filament v4+ compatibility with custom theme CSS
- Configuring dark mode with `@variant dark` in Tailwind v4
- Registering Filament custom themes with `viteTheme()` after migration

